     <profileDesc>
        <abstract><p><persName ref="#padamSingh">Padam Singh</persName>, ruler of <placeName ref="#salumbar">Salumbar</placeName> and a noble of <placeName ref="#udaipur">Udaipur</placeName>, writes to the British colonial official <persName ref="#jamesTod">James Tod</persName> announcing that a son and heir was born the previous night. 
           The letter opens with formalities expressing <persName ref="#padamSingh">Padam Singh's</persName> loyalty.<note>This is a copy of an original document received by <persName ref="#jamesTod">Tod</persName>. Two documents are copied on the same folio; this is the lower document on the page.</note></p></abstract>       
