  <text>
      <body>
         <pb n="1r" facs="lf_tod_1818_rasgbi_tod170_34.jpg"/>
         <div xml:id="orig_div1" xml:lang="eng" type="laterAddition" rend="middle centre">
            <p>Ar. 35 <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_rawat">Rawat</ref> <persName ref="#padamSingh">Paddam Sing [Padam Singh]</persName> to <choice><abbr>Col.</abbr><expan>Colonel</expan></choice> <persName ref="#jamesTod">Tod</persName><gap/></p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="orig_div2" xml:lang="raj" type="laterAddition" rend="middle centre">
            <p><placeName ref="#salumbar">सुलंबर</placeName> का रावत जी श्री <persName ref="#padamSingh">पदम सिंघ</persName> जी रा खलीता की नकल</p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="trans_div2" corresp="#orig_div2">
            <p>Copy of the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_kharita">kharita</ref> of <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_rawat">Rawat</ref> <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_jiu">Ji</ref> Shri <persName ref="#padamSingh">Padam Singh</persName> <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_jiu">Ji</ref> of <placeName ref="#salumbar">Salumbar</placeName></p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="orig_div3" xml:lang="raj" type="maintext">
            <p>
               <lb/>स्वस्ति श्री <placeName ref="#udaipur">उदैपुर</placeName> सुथाने सरब ओपमा जोग्य राजश्री <persName ref="#jamesTod">जिमस टाट</persName> साहब ब-
               <lb/>हादर जोग्य श्री <placeName ref="#salumbar">सलुंबर</placeName> थी रावत श्री <persName ref="#padamSingh">पदम सिंघ</persName> जी लिखावतं श्री राम राम बा-
               <lb/>चजो अठा रा स्माचर श्री जी री सुनिजरक रे भला छै राज रा सदा भला चाहिजै
               <lb/>तो म्हानै सुख छै म्हांरै राज सिवाय कई बात नही सदा हेत इकलास रखावो ज-
               <lb/>णी थी यादा विसेख रखावसी अप्रंच अठै <date calendar="#samvat-chaitradi">चैत बदि ३ रवे</date> ती पाछली राति पो-
               <lb/>हर डोढ रह्ता कंवर हूवो है राज चैन पावैगा अठा सरीखो कामकाज छै सो
               <lb/>लिखोगा अठा उठा रो एक ही विवहार जाणोगा <date calendar="#samvat-chaitradi"><choice><abbr>सं</abbr><expan>संवत</expan></choice> १८७५ रा चेत बदि ४ सोमे</date> 
            </p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="trans_div3" corresp="#orig_div3">
            <p>
               <lb/>Hail! [To] the incomparable eminent <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_rajashri">Rajashri</ref> <persName ref="#jamesTod">James Tod</persName> <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_sahib">Sahib</ref> <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_bahadur">Bahadur</ref> [in] the good place of Shri <placeName ref="#udaipur">Udaipur</placeName>, 
               <lb/><ref type="glossary" target="#gl_rawat">Rawat</ref> Shri <persName ref="#padamSingh">Padam Singh</persName> <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_jiu">Ji</ref> writes from the eminent Shri <placeName ref="#salumbar">Salumbar</placeName>. Proclaim Shri Ram Ram.<note>I.e., greetings.</note>
               <lb/>By the merciful attention of Shri <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_jiu">Ji</ref><note>Here, 'Shri Ji' likely refers to the ruler of <placeName ref="#udaipur">Udaipur</placeName>.</note>, the news here is good. May the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_raj">Raj</ref> always be good,
               <lb/>then I am happy. I have nothing without the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_raj">Raj</ref>. Let friendship always be kept,
               <lb/>which will be especially remembered. Therefore: here on <date calendar="#samvat-chaitradi">Chaitra <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_badi">badi</ref> 3, Sunday</date>, [when]
               <lb/>one-and-a-half <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_pahar">pahars</ref> remained last night, a <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_kunwar">kunwar</ref> was born. The <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_raj">Raj</ref> will be relieved [by this news]. When there is business here,
               <lb/>so I will write. Here and there, the same dealings will be known. <date calendar="#samvat-chaitradi">Samvat [year] 1875's Chaitra <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_badi">badi</ref> 4, Monday.</date>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
